item.title: Why Mortgage Rates Dropped After the Fed Rate Hike | Zillow Porchlight
item.description:
Why Mortgage Rates Dropped After the Fed Rate Hike | Zillow Porchlight

This month, the Federal Reserve System hiked rates for the first time in nine years. In the days since the Fed move, mortgage rates actually dropped. How is this possible? And will this trend hold as home-buyers make plans for 2016? Immediate mortgage rate reaction to Fed meeting Most U.S.
